ajaxpoll-vote-update:
System response that the vote was successfully updated.

If error, the following message is used:
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-vote-error}}

ajaxpoll-vote-add:
System response that the vote was successfully added.

If error, the following message is used:
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-vote-error}}

ajaxpoll-vote-error:
Used as error message.

If successful, the following message are used:
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-vote-update}}
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-vote-add}}
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-vote-revoked}}

ajaxpoll-no-vote:
Used if there are no votes.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-revoke-vote}}

ajaxpoll-vote-permission:
Text for viewers who do not have the right to vote.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-revoke-vote}}
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-no-vote}}

ajaxpoll-readonly:
Text for when the database is in readonly mode and the poll cannot be voted on.

Parameters:
* $1 - the reason for which the database was locked

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-vote-permission}}
* {{msg-mw|Readonlywarning}}

ajaxpoll-view-results-permission:
Used if the user is not allowed to view.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-view-results-before-vote-permission}}

ajaxpoll-view-results-before-vote-permis:
Used if the user is allowed to vote but the user has not voted.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-view-results-permission}}

ajaxpoll-revoke-vote:
Voters can revoke their vote and this is the message text to be clicked when a voter wants to revoke a previous vote.

The text is only shown for persons who already voted, in an extra line below the block of answers.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-no-vote}}
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-vote-permission}}

ajaxpoll-vote-revoked:
System response that the vote was successfully revoked.

If error, the following message is used:
* {{msg-mw|Ajaxpoll-vote-error}}
